  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Solanaceae herb from Mexico/Central America. Produces small (2–4 cm) green berries (tomatillos) within a papery calyx husk. Characterized by gametophytic self-incompatibility (GSI) requiring cross-pollination across plants. Self-incompatible flowers are hermaphrodite but genetically prevent self-fertility; cross-compatibility occurs across genotypes at an S-locus. The only self-incompatible Physalis species commonly cultivated.",
  "name": "Physalis philadelphica",
